The paper proposes a deep-learning-based approach for matrix completion, which is a common problem in recommender systems and other big data applications. The approach combines geometric matrix completion models with conditional random fields (CRFs) and uses a deep model to predict missing entries by solving the MAP inference problem. This work involves machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures (cs.DS), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
